# Teaching: Signal — Lug Triage Presentation Protocol v1

**Type:** signal
**safe_to_auto_adopt:** true

---

## What This Teaching Does

Appends a high-impact behavioral signal to the spoke's lug store. Instructs all AI agents on how to present open lugs for user review: grouping, enumeration, 4-column format, auto-inferred titles, and SEV verification gate.

---

## Why It Matters

Raw lug IDs (e.g. `lug-bulk-6`, UUID strings) and system-generated titles carry no recall value for the user. Without a structured format, agents present backlogs as noise. Without a SEV gate, agents assign `implement` or `close` verdicts to items they cannot actually describe or verify — silently burying scope gaps.

---

